"List / stream-processing benchmark (workload class H). A range → map →
sum pipeline over a lazy list. Frozen from review C's suggested class-H
probe. Both engines are O(n^2) here (the shared env-walk ceiling,
ROADMAP; review A D5), so N is tuned to 6000 to land in the >1s band
rather than a round figure -- the value is the bc/hs comparison on the
shared ceiling, not raw throughput. Runs >1s on the faster engine."

# sum of (i + 1) for i in 0..5999  ==  sum 1..6000  ==  18003000
grand: range(0, 6000) map(_ + 1) sum

` { target: :bench-list-scale
    verify: ["default-expectation"] }
bench-list-scale: {
  total: grand
  RESULT: if(grand = 18003000, :PASS, :FAIL)
}
